//Smith when to a Mall to play a balloon game where his has to shoot 2 kinds of balloon which are colored: White & Red. White balloon carries 1 point and Red balloon carries 2 points. Smith shot certain no. of White and Red balloons in the game. Find and print the total no. of scores he makes in this game.

//Input Format
//In First input line, enter total number of White balloons shot. In Second input line, enter total number of Red balloons shot.

//Constraints
//Enter only integer (positive) value. 0<=n<=100

//Output Format
//Print the total no. of scores Smith makes in this game. If any input is given negative, then total scores should be counted as 0.



import java.io.*;
import java.util.*;
import java.text.*;
import java.math.*;
import java.util.regex.*;

public class Solution {

    public static void main(String[] args) {
        /* Enter your code here. Read input from STDIN. Print output to STDOUT. Your class should be named Solution. */
        Scanner s=new Scanner(System.in);
        int a,b;
        a=s.nextInt();
        b=s.nextInt();
        if(a<=100 & a>=0 & b<=100 & b>=0){
            System.out.println((a*1)+(b*2) );
        }
        else if(a<0 || b<0){
            System.out.println("0");
        }
    }
}
